    "created_at": "2024-05-25T14:02:58Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-05-25T14:02:58Z",
    "body": "> I'm also having the same issue.\r\n\r\nHi @CodeConnoisseur74 I fixed the issue my installing https://packages.gentoo.org/packages/media-fonts/noto-emoji .\r\nThe issue was not git_state but rather the directory module. /etc/portage was a readonly directory for my user so the directory module by defaults shows a lock symbol which I did not have support.\r\n\r\nYou can fix it by either installing a emoji supported font or by changing the directory module to show text instead of the read only symbol, ie. \"RO\"",
